<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>veeshanMurtak</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Mystic<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jan 2004<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>This is my summary of 6 months worth of discussion, analysis and polls on the Crucible. I will probably edit in some links to some of those later.<br />
<br />
This post is mainly going to address the issues of elemental+ shamans. Some of the changes will of course benefit lower level or lower AAd shamans as well. Overall however I believe that most shaman problems concern the post-elemental part of the game and thus this proposal is centered on fixing shaman issues in that content.<br />
<br />
<b><u>General Shaman issues:</u></b><br />
* Shamans have received less upgrades to every single one of their spell lines then all other classes got to their comparable spell lines for every expansion since Kunark. Shamans want at least some of that lost power back. This includes DoTs, nukes, cannibalize (already being adressed), buffs (partially being adressed), heals and pets.<br />
* Shamans suffer more then any other class from the short fights of LDoN and GoD (and to a lesser degree PoP) as well as suffering more then other classes from slow mitigation. Shamans want increases to their healing to at least partially make up for the lost power of slow.<br />
* Shamans still stack poorly on raids. This can probably be adressed (or mostly adressed) by the improvements outlined above.<br />
* DoT aggro is utterly out of control. DoT aggro should be decreased to the level of an equally damaging direct damage.<br />
<br />
<b><u>Specific shaman issues</u></b><br />
* When acting as a healer shamans rely on slow to be able to heal at all. Any resist causes the shaman to go into chain healing mode which will at best negate the incoming damage. There is no time to attempt to slow again, which is what shaman healing as balanced around. Shamans would like an emergency ability (most likely as an AA skill) to address this.<br />
* The shaman group haste is still inferior to the single target spell.<br />
* Shamans are still unable to shrink their pets.<br />
* The Avatar line has an effect which is not even close to being in line with the mana and time required to use it (not to mention having to lose a spell gem to it). This is even more pronounced as players cap their stats.<br />
<br />
That being said this is the list of specifics:<br />
<i>(Items of minor interest to either the majority of shamans or of low balance impact are in italics. Critical issues are bolded.)</i><br />
<br />
<br />
<font size="4">Healing</font><br />
<b>* Spot Heal</b><br />
Improve Daluda's Mending to heal 1900 damage. Increase the mana cost to 600. (Also adjust the OoW heal accordingly.)<br />
<br />
* Group Heal<br />
Add a shaman group HoT. It should heal 420 points per tick (same as Quiescence) and cost 900 mana.<br />
<br />
<b>* Emergency Heal</b><br />
Add a Spirit Shifting AA in three levels (4/4/4 points at levels 61/63/65). This ability will drain 12/25/40% of the shaman's HPs and give them to his current target. The casting time should be no higher then 1 second. The reuse time should be 10 minutes.<br />
<br />
<br />
<font size="4">Mana Regeneration</font><br />
<b>* Cannibalize</b><br />
Shaman spells are balanced on the assumption that shamans regenerate mana much faster then other classes. As other classes have received a much larger increase to their mana regeneration over the last expansions then shamans did shaman mana regeneration is in need of an upgrade. This can come either in the form of more efficient cannibalize spells or in the form of cannibalize spells that basically combine several castings of cannibalize into one big cast, thus freeing up time for other tasks.<br />
The current ancient cannibalize spell is a good spell, but something so central to the shaman class should not be available to a select few. Make the new cannibalize spell a purchaseable spell in PoK.<br />
<br />
<br />
<font size="4">Damage</font><br />
<b>* DoT aggro</b><br />
Decrease DoT aggro significantly. A DoT that does 2000 damage should not add more aggro then a direct damage spell that does 2000 damage.<br />
<br />
* Poison nukes<br />
Increase Spear of Torment to do 900 damage. Up the mana cost to 370.<br />
<br />
* Ice nukes<br />
Increase Velium Strike to do 1300 damage. Up the mana cost to 430.<br />
<br />
* Poison DoTs<br />
Increase Blood of Saryrn to do 400 damage per tick. Up the mana cost to 650 to match that increase. Add a -30 resist adjustment. (Also change the OoW poison DoT accordingly. Also apply the resist adjustment to lower level poison DoTs.)<br />
<br />
* Magic DoTs<br />
Increase Bane to do 500 damage per tick. Up the mana cost to 600. Add a -60 resist adjustment. (Apply equivalent changes to the other spells of this line.)<br />
<br />
<br />
<font size="4">Debuffs</font><br />
* Balance of the Nihil<br />
Up the resist modifier on Balance of the Nihil to -55 to match Malos.<br />
<br />
<br />
<font size="4">Buffs</font><br />
* Avoidance<br />
The replacement buff for our agility line has a listed effect of 7% avoidance. In actual play this seems to work out to an actual 4% avoidance. It should be improved to 10% (listed) to produce an actual 6% avoidance effect in game.<br />
<br />
* Damage<br />
The replacement buff for our strength line has a listed effect of 5% melee damage. In actual play this seems to work out to an actual 2% damage. It should be improved to 10% (listed) to produce an actual 4% damage effect in game.<br />
<br />
* HPs<br />
The OoW shaman stamina buff currently adds stamina past the stat cap. Shamans fear that stamina will suffer from additional dimishing returns past 305. If the spell ends up adding less then 200 HPs to a stat-capped 65 warrior it should be removed in favor of a non-capped effect, similar to the other buff replacements (stun resist or shielding seem appropriate).<br />
<br />
* Focus<br />
Increase the HPs on the OoW version of the focus line to 850. Remove the strength and dexterity components and replace them with +melee damage to match the standalone buff.<br />
<br />
* Focus<br />
Increase the HPs on Focus of Soul to 650.<br />
<br />
* Avatar<br />
The effect of the avatar line is not at all in line with its cost. Either substantially up the effects of this spell line, add a group version of the spell or substantially up the duration.<br />
<br />
* <i>Group haste</i><br />
The shaman group haste is inferior to the single target spell. Up the haste to match that of the single target version.<br />
<br />
<font size="4">Misc</font><br />
* <i>Pet</i><br />
Make the shaman pet innately dual weild (currently it dual weilds once given weapons).<br />
<br />
* <i>Pet shrink</i><br />
Make the shaman pet shrinkable again.<br />
<br />
<br />
--<i> Adjust other spells accordingly" means that the spell in question should receive the same percentual improvements compared to the base spell as comparable spells of other classes get in that expansion. </i>--<br />
<br />
<i>reposted per request - /wave Gloriana</i></p>
	
	
	
